## emberbeta (local)

### Local dev

Install deps:

- `npm install`

Run the app:

- `npm run dev`

### Talk (Hume EVI speech-to-speech) â€” local only

This repo uses a tiny local Node WebSocket proxy so your Hume API key never ships to the browser.

1) Create a `.env` in the repo root:

- Copy `server/HUME_ENV.example` into `.env`
- Fill in:
  - `HUME_API_KEY` (rotate/revoke any leaked keys first)
  - `HUME_EVI_CONFIG_ID` (your saved Ember EVI config id from Hume)

2) Start the proxy + Vite:

- `npm run dev:all`

Notes:

- Default proxy WS is `ws://localhost:8788/evi`
- If you change the proxy port (`EVI_PROXY_PORT`), set a matching frontend WS URL via:
  - `VITE_EVI_PROXY_WS=ws://localhost:<port>/evi`
- In `Talk`, click the orb to request mic permissions + start the voice session. Mute/end call still work.
